<h2>The weather in October 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
The main part of Europe was dominated by high pressure weather in October. Average temperatures were therefore above the 1981-2010 average in large parts of the continent. Especially eastern Europe and Italy encountered exceptionally high temperatures, during both day and night. The northern part of Scandinavia and some parts of Spain and Germany had below average minimum temperatures (Figures 6 and 7). Figure 8 and 9 show that the western part of Europe experienced both exceptionally high temperatures at the warmest day and below or exceptionally low temperatures during the coldest night.
